Same for `handleCpf`

Also, the value of the `TextField` is in `e.text` not in `e.currentTarget.value`, [here](https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/textinput#onchange) is the documentation.

Alternatively, you can use `onChangeText`, that gives you the value directly, for example:
```js
&lt;TextField
   // ...
   onChangeText={this.handleEmail.bind(this)}
